62.6	Electrocardiography	Electrocardiography	Electrocardiography is a transthoracic (across the thorax or chest) interpretation of the electrical activity of the heart over a period of time, as detected by electrodes attached to the outer surface of the skin and recorded by a device external to the body. The recording produced by this noninvasive procedure is termed as electrocardiogram (also ECG or EKG). An electrocardiogram (ECG) is a test that records the electrical activity of the heart.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/ECGcolor.svg/230px-ECGcolor.svg.png
